<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-502-293  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 502 293.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  Oct 9 1990 v4 n34 p20(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>SimCity gets worldly companion, add-ons. (Maxis simulationcomputer games) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Norr, Henry.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Maxis (product introduction)Broderbund Software Inc. (distribution).andO;Product:   SimCity Graphic Set 2 - Future Cities (Add-in-on software)(product introduction)SimCity Graphic Set 1 - Ancient Cities (Add-in-on software)(product introduction)SimEarth - The Living Planet (Computer game) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Add-In-On SoftwareDistribution AgreementsComputer GamesSimulation.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Maxis' SimEarth simulates evolutionandM;By Henry NorrandM;Moraga, Calif.andP;  -- Maxis, the company responsible for the popular SimCityurban simulation game, is preparing a sequel that could give new meaning tothe term &quot;power user.&quot;andM;SimEarth -- The Living Planet lets players manipulate the evolution of lifefrom its origins in the ocean to the onset of the Nanotech Age, changing theshape of continents and oceans, laying down forests, jungles and deserts,introducing animal species, and loosing plagues on unsuspecting populations.andO;If all else fails, the user can even abandon Earth and play a Mars or Venusscenario.andM;Like its predecessor, SimEarth will be marketed primarily as entertainmentsoftware, but it also is likely to be widely used as a tool for educationabout natural history and environmental issues.andP;  &quot;It's a good review of theevolutionary process, and it's got an excellent manual -- as good as manyschool courses,&quot; said beta-tester David Anderson of Gaia Corp. in Burbank,Calif.andP;  Anderson produced &quot;Voice of the Planet,&quot; a 10-hour series about theGaia hypothesis that will be shown on the Turner Broadcasting System nextweek.andM;Due next month, SimEarth will be priced at $69.95 and distributed byBroderbund Software Inc.andM;In addition, Maxis announced several related products that are scheduled forrelease this month:andM;andgt;&quot;The SimCity Planning Commission Handbook&quot; by Johnny L. Wilson explains thegame, offers a history of cities and describes real-life urban-planningproblems and ways players can explore alternative solutions with SimCitymodels.andP;  Published by McGraw-Hill Publishing Co., the book will bedistributed through major booksellers for $14.95.andM;andgt;Two SimCity add-ons let users build cities set in times and places notsupported by the original SimCity or by Maxis' Terrain Editor.andP;  Graphic Set 1-- Ancient Cities incorporates buildings and technologies from ancient Asia,medieval times and the Wild West.andP;  Graphic Set 2 -- Future Cities opens awindow on future urban life in the United States, Europe and a moon colony,complete with fusion plants, space travel and a creeping acidic fungus.andM;Each set will be priced at $34.95.andM;Maxis is located at 1042 Country Club Drive, Suite C, Moraga, Calif.andP;  94556;(415) 376-6434.andM;Broderbund Software Inc. is at 17 Paul Drive, San Rafael, Calif.andP;  94903-2101;(415) 492-3200.andO;</TEXT></DOC>